18/05/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- Macedonian Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski reiterated his country's support for UN envoy Martti Ahtisaari's Kosovo status plan on Thursday (May 17th). 
He added that he hopes Macedonia and Kosovo would soon resolve their border demarcation issue. 
Gruevski visited Pristina for talks with UNMIK chief Joachim Ruecker and Kosovo counterpart Agim Ceku. 
Gruevski stressed he would expect co-operation between Macedonia and Kosovo, especially in the areas of transport and communication, to increase considerably after the status issue is resolved.
Albanian Foreign Minister Lulzim Basha paid a separate visit to Pristina on Thursday, stressing that Kosovo's eventual independence is crucial to regional stability. 
Meeting with Ruecker, Basha predicted that members of the UN Security Council would approve Ahtisaari's plan. 
(Kohajone, Korrieri - 18/05/07; Top-Channel, Telegrafi, Tanjug, MIA, Makfax - 17/05/07)
